text:
Environment is hot.

The meat? ðŸ˜…
I ordered Roast Pork, Char Siew, Roast Duck, Roast Chicken, the meat is super ordinary.. I believe many of the stall outside would beat their meat hands down.

Fragrant Rice, no much fragrant.
The meat dry and hard.

Would never trust this brand anymore.

Food is ok, pricing is odd.

Roast duck rice is $4.50.

Roast duck rice, with extra duck is $6.50 (add $2).

Charsiew and roast pork rice is $5.30.

Charsiew, roast pork and roast duck rice is $9.30 (add $4??).

The additional duck costs an extra $4 but the portion of extra duck meat is half of the $4.50 roast duck rice.

The duck is good. Whole duck $20. But it's tough

This packet of duck and char siew with rice $6.30. char siew is flavourful but a bit tough. Achar is a nice addition
There was more duck meat than what you usually get at other stalls. The taste was okay, but nothing special to shout about.

While the food is quite nice, their noodle portion is KID SIZED. finished in a few mouthfuls. Totally not filling

And their meat is inedible because almost all are pure FATS!

Paid $4.50 for roasted pork noodle is already quite ex, but now you cant even eat the meat so imagine paying 4.50 for plain noodles?! Cutthroat..
